HP3 : Norm Strength


Does higher norm strength lead to higher norm compliance?


How did we compute Norm Strength Index?


\[Strength = {NE_{avg} \over NE_{sd}}\] where:

  • \(Delta_{avg} = NE_{avg} - Coop_{avg}\)
  • \(NE_{sd}\) is the standard deviation of means of KW appropriateness score (for each scenarios)


Summary of Norm strength

   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
  0.000   1.046   1.687   1.985   2.900   4.065


Distribution


Results


    Spearman's rank correlation rho

data:  Strenght_stat_df$Strength_N and Strenght_stat_df$Delta_Avg
S = 1754.9, p-value = 0.5454
alternative hypothesis: true rho is not equal to 0
sample estimates:
     rho 
0.132938

Note: without outliers
